<p class="summary">Watching wildlife and being in nature can have health benefits. Here&rsquo;s what to watch out for in January.</p>

<p>January in the North of the world can sometimes be a little grim. As we are tilted further away from the Sun, our light is less frequent and dimmer, compared to our summer months. However, there are still little sources of brightness to be found in our natural world. Keeping a look out for these plants and animals can focus our mind on the little treasures in this cold grey time, and remind us of the brightness to come.</p>

