<h2>2. Snowdrops</h2>

<p>While robins can be seen all year round, there are flowers that pop up only around Winter. I find the first signs of snowdrops to be particularly special as they signify a change in the seasons, an end to winter and the start of the new year&rsquo;s abundance.</p>
<p>I love the names of snow drops. In French there&rsquo;s &ldquo;snow piercer&rdquo; or &ldquo;perce-neige&rdquo; due to the way the plant pierces its way up through the winter snow. While Spanish has &ldquo;little bells&rdquo; or &ldquo;snowflakes&rdquo; from &ldquo;campanillas&rdquo; or &ldquo;copos de nieve.&rdquo;</p>
<p>Seeing their little white metals now drops fill me with hope and excitement as it signals all the flowers and little natural wonders to come. I&rsquo;m lucky that some have been planted in the green spaces where I live, but you might have to explore some of your local green spaces to find them.</p>

