<h2>3. Hellebores</h2>

<p>My other favourite winter flower are hellebores. I find they have a certain magical quality to them, firstly because of how they can bloom in winter when everything else is frozen, and the second is their mystical colour.</p>
<p>I know of very few plants that have green flower heads, and hellebores can have a particularly ethereal light green to them. These large petals are actually sepals, which protect the flowers, with the petals significantly smaller hiding in the center. You can also find them in fantastic deep purples, light pinks, bright yellows and whites.</p>

